Harris is not someone with a political track record as a barnstorming progr=
essive on economic issues,=E2=80=9D Smith said. =E2=80=9CIs she a Bernie Sa=
nders-style progressive, a soak-the-rich type? Is that who she is? Is she a=
 corporate Democrat, a Wall Street kind of person? Voters just don't know. =
So again, there is opportunity there, but there is vulnerability there if R=
epublicans can seize it. She needs to define herself first and foremost on =
the economy, and particularly on prices.=E2=80=9D

Some of that is already happening, as Smith acknowledged. =E2=80=9CShe=E2=
=80=99s talking about inflation,=E2=80=9D he noted. =E2=80=9CIt=E2=80=99s i=
n the campaign ads, this champion of working family stuff. It=E2=80=99s abs=
olutely the right direction to go. But she has to acknowledge the pain that=
 people are in. To say, =E2=80=98I do acknowledge our economy is not perfec=
t, and I can tell you why. It=E2=80=99s these greedy A-holes who I have a h=
istory with. But I will be on your team again.=E2=80=99=E2=80=9D

