           <p style=3D"margin: 0; color: #000000; font-size: 16px; line-hei=
ght: 30px; margin-top: 15px; margin-bottom: 0;">Welcome back to The Best &a=
mp; The Brightest. I=E2=80=99m <b>Peter Hamby</b>. Tonight, a look at the n=
ext chapter in the battle to define <b>Kamala Harris</b>=E2=80=94the questi=
on of how she=E2=80=99ll handle the economy. Harris is already addressing c=
oncerns about her immigration record head-on, trying to neutralize her bigg=
est vulnerability with voters and deflect slashing attacks from <b>Donald T=
rump</b>=E2=80=99s campaign. But Harris also has to capitalize on the goodw=
ill she has with voters <i>right now</i>, and convince them that she feels =
their pain=E2=80=94and that Trump would be worse for their pocketbooks.<br/=
><br/><i>But first, <b>Abby Livingston</b> captures the mood on Capitol Hil=
l=E2=80=A6</i><br/></p>
